Α striking proof of this principle is afforded by the cities in the southwestern district of Pisidia, or according to Byzantine arrangement in the province of Pamphylia Secunda.

Hierocles begins his list of the Pamphylian cities with the western part of Pamphylia proper, i. e. the coast-land south of mount Taurus. He then passes by Termessus, which lies on the pass over Mount Taurus, to the highlands of Pisidia, and enumeratos the cities of the Taurus valley as follows:
